  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Traumatic sesamoid displacement of the first metacarpophalangeal joint can affect thumb
      function.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Although occurrence is rare, the mechanism of the displacement is commonly complex and
      varied. Understanding the mechanism is critical for treatment of the disorder. We herein
      present a locked thumb MCPJ caused by sesamoid displacement.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
